    soilGeologyPara: "Manhattan schist and Fordham gneiss surface within 20 feet of grade across Midtown and the Upper West Side, while Queens and Brooklyn ride glacial moraine mixed with uncompacted harbor fill. The Red Hook waterfront, Lower Manhattan landfill, and Battery Park City all sit on 19th-century fill that continues settling measurably each decade. Hunts Point in the Bronx includes buried tidal marsh peat that produces differential movement distinct from nearby upland blocks, and NYC DOB geotechnical reports often flag these zones before issuing underpinning permits.",
