    localGeologyPara: `Expansive Pennsylvanian shale with PI values of 35 to 50 underlies most of the metro, and the Missouri-Kansas state line splits the market into two separate permit-license-code jurisdictions. A Brookside project follows KCMO building code while identical scope in Overland Park follows Johnson County, Kansas regulations. The May 2024 supercell dropped baseball-sized hail across Johnson County, and the severe hail corridor produces 3 to 5 significant events per year that damage foundation-adjacent equipment. Evergy and Spire gas serve the Missouri side; Kansas Gas Service operates across the state line.`,
    repairMethodPara: `Concrete pressed pilings at 15 to 22 feet through expansive shale to Kansas City Group limestone are the metro standard at $375 to $500 per pier through KC Pier and Foundation Support Specialists. Contractors must hold both Missouri and Kansas registrations to serve the full metro. KCMO Permits and Inspections issues permits on the Missouri side while Johnson County and Wyandotte County handle the Kansas side with different fee schedules. Country Club Plaza, Pendleton Heights, and Janssen Place fall under the KCMO Historic Preservation Commission; Kansas-side municipalities have limited historic protections.`,
    drainageAndMoisturePara: `Kansas City's 39 inches of rain concentrates in April through June severe thunderstorms that deliver 2 to 4 inches in under two hours, and the expansive shale amplifies damage by swelling rapidly under sudden saturation. KC Water manages the combined sewer on the Missouri side, and Johnson County Wastewater handles the Kansas side, each with different overflow thresholds and backwater-valve rebate programs. Hard water at 150 to 200 ppm drives mineral deposits on drain tile.`,
