    localGeologyPara: `The White River floodplain produces flat terrain where Wisconsinan glacial till 10 to 20 feet thick overlies Silurian-Devonian limestone, giving Indianapolis uniform bearing capacity that contrasts with Pittsburgh's hillside complexity. IMI (Irving Materials Inc.) headquartered in nearby Greenfield operates limestone quarries and ready-mix plants that provide shorter material lead times than any competing metro. Very hard water at 250 to 350 ppm from Citizens Water is the highest mineral content among these 10 metros, driving aggressive scale buildup on every drainage component.`,
