    drainageAndMoisturePara: `Indianapolis receives 42 inches of rain spread evenly year-round, and the White River floodplain through Broad Ripple keeps the water table within 6 to 8 feet of grade during spring snowmelt. The 250-to-350-ppm extremely hard water drives the most aggressive mineral scaling of any metro on this list, requiring annual drain-tile and check-valve flushing. The DigIndy tunnel system is actively reducing combined sewer overflows across near-downtown neighborhoods like Fountain Square and Fletcher Place.`,
