    localGeologyPara: `Nashville Basin limestone and Ordovician phosphatic clay coexist within the same lot, with 3 to 8 feet of reactive clay over fractured bedrock through Germantown and East Nashville. The March 2020 EF3 tornado carved a 60-mile path through East Nashville, Germantown, Donelson, and Mt. Juliet, damaging thousands of foundations. The metro's explosive 3 to 4 percent growth rate has created severe labor scarcity in the foundation-repair trade. NES provides electric service, and Piedmont Natural Gas handles the gas side.`,
